My meme

The main component of this inspo meme that I changed in my meme was the text, the original inspo meme was a picture of Mr. Incredible smiling, and I wanted to put a stats twist on this so I portrayed him as a happy first year student getting into stats. I went further into this trope with my animation by adding multiple slides with Mr. Incredible

# pasting the images in
incredible_image <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/the-canny-incredible/images/1/17/Image_phase_1_mr_incredible_becoming_uncanny_by_abbysek_dex8liy-fullview.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/250?cb=20230830150538") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# creating and annotating the meme
frame1 <- incredible_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "stats is gonna be such an enjoyable major :)", size = 25, gravity = "north", color = "white") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

# creating an animation
image_animate(frames, fps = 0.4)

Mr Incredible reacting to stats papers

Creativity

I used multiple methods to demonstrate creativity within this project. Firstly, I edited the css code to change the colors of my webpage in order to make it more personal to myself and aesthetically pleasing. I also related the meme to stats at UOA, showcasing the levels of difficulty of stats courses through varying images of Mr. Incredible. The original meme shows a happy face of Mr. Incredible, and I added text and changed the images of the gif to portray him becoming increasingly more uncanny in relation to how difficult the stats course is.

Learning reflection

An important idea that I learnt from this project was the idea that combining multiple data technologies such as css and html would be able to create aesthetically pleasing and useful web pages. It also allows for creativity within coding. I also learnt how enjoyable coding could be, because with my stats 201 course I only felt frustration, this was the first time coding felt rewarding and creative.

On the other hand, one part of stats 201 that I did enjoy was visualising data through code, I would like to delve deeper into that while also adding the creative side to data visualisation. I feel like it will be a valuable skill to have in the workforce while also being very enjoyable.
